<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870608-0138 </DOCNO><HL> Letters to the Editor:Airbus Pact Facts</HL><DD> 06/08/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> EUROP TEX NWAAEROSPACE (ARO)AIRLINES (AIR) </IN><TEXT>   Your May 14 article &quot;Boeing's Accord With Allegis Reflects Stiff Competition Among Aircraft Firms&quot; states: &quot;More recently, Airbus has aggressively entered into financing pacts with Eastern, Continental and Northwest Airlines.&quot;    The facts: The Airbus/Eastern deal was made nine years ago, hardly recent. Nonetheless, Airbus's financial exposure is not that dissimilar from that of other manufacturers. Airbus Industrie's financing support with Continental is very similar to that offered by other manufacturers. And Airbus provides no financing support for Northwest. At the announcement of the purchase of up to 100 A-320 aircraft last October, NWA Chairman and Chief Executive Officer Steven G. Rothmeier said, &quot;There are no financing arrangements. We will be financing the aircraft ourselves.&quot;    David C. Venz   Vice President, Communications   Airbus Industrie   Herndon, Va.</TEXT></DOC>